n the empty string.\n\nThe empty string can be \"decoded\" as either zero or two copies of itself,\nviolating unique decodability. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/InformationTheory/Coding/UniquelyDecodable.html#InformationTheory.UniquelyDecodable.epsilon_not_mem","kind":"theorem","line":42,"name":"InformationTheory.UniquelyDecodable.epsilon_not_mem","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/InformationTheory/Coding/UniquelyDecodable.lean#L42-L49"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/InformationTheory/Coding/UniquelyDecodable.html#InformationTheory.UniquelyDecodable\"><span class=\"name\">InformationTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">UniquelyDecodable</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A set of lists is uniquely decodable if distinct concatenations yield distinct strings. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/InformationTheory/Coding/UniquelyDecodable.html#InformationTheory.UniquelyDecodable","kind":"def","line":34,"name":"InformationTheory.UniquelyDecodable","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/InformationTheory/Coding/UniquelyDecodable.lean#L34-L38"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Data.Set.Basic"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.InformationTheory.Coding.UniquelyDecodable"}